==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪə(r)|-aɪə(r)]]

===Preposition===
'''prior'''

#[[before]]

====Usage note====
Generally suffixed with "to", as in:  prior to.  This word is often seen as causing confusion and using "before" instead of "prior to" has often been recommended.

===Noun===
'''prior''' (plural: ''priors'')

#{{law}} a previous criminal offense on someone's record

